pr_title: Milestone 1.1 : Update the documentation for End-To-End tests and Debug End-To-End wiki page.
pr_body:
Added the documentation for:
* Debug End to End tests in webdriverio
* End to End tests in webdriverio
* Hybrid mode

pr_title: Milestone 1.2 (Migrate away from protractor): Setup webdriverio and migrate few tests suite from protractor to webdriverIO
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

Setup webdriverIO for running e2e tests, write eslint rules for webdriverIO suites to make sure the code quality is maintained, and write a backend tests to ensure the union of suites present in both versions is a complete list of e2e suites, and migrate the following tests:

**Suites Covered:**
* Collections
* Learner
* User
* ProfileFeatures

**Utils Covered:**
* CreatorDashboardPage (Partial)
* CollectionEditorPage (Complete)
* LibraryPage (Partial)
* AdminPage (Partial)
* ExplorationEditorPage (Partial)
* ExplorationPlayerPage (Partial)
* LearnerDashboardPage (Partial)
* ModeratorPage (Complete)
* PreferencesPage (Partial)
* ProfilePage (Complete)

Also this PR migrates action.js, forms.js, general.js, waitFor.js and all the interactions in extensions/** folder.


## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Milestone 1.3 (Migrate away from protractor): Migrated few test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->
Migrated the following test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
**Suites Covered:**
* Subscription
* Preferences
* CreatorDashboard
* LearnerDashboard
**Utils Covered:**
* CreatorDashboard (Partial)
* PreferencesPage (Complete)
* SubscriptionDashboardPage (Complete)
* ExplorationEditorPage (Partial)
* ExplorationPlayerPage (Partial)
* LearnerDashboardPage (Partial)
* AdminPage (Partial)
* TopicEditorPage (Partial)
* StoryEditorPage (Partial)
* SkillEditorPage (Partial)
* LibraryPage (Partial)
* TopicAndStoryViewerPage (Partial)
* TopicsAndSkillsDashboardPage (Partial)


## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

pr_title: Milestone 1.4 (Migrate away from protractor): Migrated few test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->
Migrate the following test suite from protractor to webdriverIO. 
**Suites Covered:**
* ProfileMenu
* TopicAndStoryViewer
* TopicAndStoryEditor

**Utils Covered:**
* LearnerDashboardPage (Complete)
* AdminPage (Partial)
* TopicsAndSkillsDashboardPage (Partial)
* TopicAndStoryViewerPage (Complete)
* TopicViewerPage (Complete)
* TopicEditorPage (Partial)
* StoryEditorPage (Partial)
* SubTopicViewerPage (Complete)
* ExplorationEditorPage (Partial)
* ExplorationPlayerPage (Partial)
* SkillEditorPage (Partial)

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

```
<select>
  <option>
  <option>
</select>
```

So it means any code like:
``` 
var option = $(`option=${Text}`);
```
can be replace with selectByVisibleText(). But this function(pageToFullyLoad) is just for waiting for the page load to finish ( which indirectly means wait for the invisbility of loading message)?

P.S For me the underlying problem for the learnerdashboard flake lies in these two below lines.
```
var loadingMessage = $('.e2e-test-loading-fullpage');
await browser.waitUntil(
  await until.invisibilityOf(loadingMessage),
  {
    timeout: 15000,
    timeoutMsg: 'Page takes more than 15 secs to load'
  });
```
$('.e2e-test-loading-fullpage'); seems to return no element found error repeatedly ([link](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/runs/7379877212?check_suite_focus=true#step:13:5067)) and because we are waiting for the invisiblity of that element in the next line, that's why the promise seem to be not resolved here(hence passing in other tests where this pattern is not followed). According to [webdriverio waiting feature](https://webdriver.io/docs/autowait/#implicit-vs-explicit), it says that default timeout is 0 and thus the promise doesn't get resolved and throws a no element found error immediatedly at some places. One possible recommendation from my side is to use the [Built in waiting provided by webdriverio](https://webdriver.io/docs/autowait/#built-in-waiting) which is the most recommended one too as suggested by webdriverio docs. 

/cc @seanlip @U8NWXD If you are also debugging the learner dashboard flake.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 24, 18, 56, 5, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'SAEb-ai', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928301907, 'comment_body': 'Just confirming that we are not currently debugging this flake (we have many others to work on).', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 24, 19, 24, 41, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'seanlip', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928304285, 'comment_body': "Oops!! That's why I pinged both of you.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 24, 19, 46, 49, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'SAEb-ai', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928474597, 'comment_body': 'waitForExists  returns true if the selector matches at least one element that exists in the DOM, otherwise throws an error. If the reverse flag is true, the command will instead return true if the selector does not match any elements. So here it is working as an invisivibilityOf function. PTAL [here](https://webdriver.io/docs/api/element/waitForExist)', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 25, 5, 10, 7, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ShivamJhaa', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928488226, 'comment_body': "Okay!! Thanks!! But I still think the underlying problem lies in` var loadingMessage = $('.e2e-test-loading-fullpage');`. The moment` waitFor.pageToLoadFully` is called findElements start getting polled for this element `$('.e2e-test-loading-fullpage');`. But as default timeout as pointed by me is 0, thus the promise doesn't get resolved as no element is found. Also, if you carefully see the [error log](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/runs/7379877212?check_suite_focus=true#step:13:5067), right after the `var loadingMessage = $('.e2e-test-loading-fullpage');` there is no execution of invisbityof command and the execution directly comes out of the pageToLoadfully which makes me more confident that the problem lies in ` var loadingMessage = $('.e2e-test-loading-fullpage');`.
`
It's different from the other cases because in other cases the selectors are mostly defined at the top and then used directly inside waitForExsits and thus findElements are being polled inside waitForExisit in this case and not directly in $ selectors which are defined at the top. Can you also please confirm this? We need the terminologies in order to avoid the future flakes of this kind too.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 7, 25, 5, 43, 57, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'SAEb-ai', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 928492087, 'comment_body': 'I also thinks the same, but can we do this debugging in some other PR, also the changes done for removing the flake is helping the other test to pass like blogDashboard so I think we should keep the changes.

pr_title: Milestone 1.5 (Migrate away from protractor): Migrated few test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

Migrate the following test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
**Suites Covered:**
* TopicAndStoryEditorFileUploadFeatures
* BlogDashBoard
* ContributorDashboard

**Utils Covered:**
* TopicsAndSkillsDashboardPage (Partial)
* TopicEditorPage (Partial)
* StoryEditorPage (Complete)
* SkillEditorPage (Partial)
* BlogDashboardPage (Complete)
* ExplorationEditorPage (Partial)
* ContributorDashboardPage (Complete)
* ContributorDashboardAdminPage (Complete)
* ExplorationEditorPage (Partial)


## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct

Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->


## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

### Note:
This PR is revert PR for the revert of PR #15726, the reason for revert was the introduction of two flakes in the develop.
* Blog dashboard functionality should create, publish, and delete the published blog post from dashboard.
    Error: Delete blog post button is not visible.
    https://github.com/oppia/oppia/runs/7620572954?check_suite_focus=true
Reason: While going sliding between the tabs, somtimes click was happening in between the transition only due to which Delete button was not visible.
Solution: Wait till the transition is complete, and then only click on the button that opens the dropdown for delete button.
* Error: Create Blog Post button is not visible.
   https://github.com/oppia/oppia/runs/7599678855?check_suite_focus=true
Reason: Webdriverio was clicking on the back button when the server was saving the blog as draft due to which an alert used to opens up which results in the error.
Solution: We are waiting for the success toast to disappear in order to make sure the blog post is saved as draft before clicking on the back button

and remove all the sections below.
-->


## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Contributing-code-to-Oppia#instructions-for-making-a-code-change).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia%27s-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-your-build-fails).

### Note:
This PR is revert PR for the revert of PR #15726, the reason for revert was the introduction of two flakes in the develop.
* Blog dashboard functionality should create, publish, and delete the published blog post from dashboard.
    Error: Delete blog post button is not visible.
    https://github.com/oppia/oppia/runs/7620572954?check_suite_focus=true
Reason: While going sliding between the tabs, somtimes click was happening in between the transition only due to which Delete button was not visible.
Solution: Wait till the transition is complete, and then only click on the button that opens the dropdown for delete button.
* Error: Create Blog Post button is not visible.
   https://github.com/oppia/oppia/runs/7599678855?check_suite_focus=true
Reason: Webdriverio was clicking on the back button when the server was saving the blog as draft due to which an alert used to opens up which results in the error.
Solution: We are waiting for the success toast to disappear in order to make sure the blog post is saved as draft before clicking on the back button

pr_title: Milestone 2.1 and 2.2 (Migrate away from protractor): Migrated few test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

Migrate the following test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
**Suites Covered:**
* AdditonalEditorFeatures
* AdditonalEditorFeaturesModals
* AdditionalPlayerFeatures
* Accessibility
* AdminPage
* CoreEditorAndPlayerFeatures

**Utils Covered:**
* ExplorationEditorPage (Partial)
* ExplorationPlayerPage (Partial)
* LibraryPage (Partial)
* AdminPage (Partial)
* CreatorDashboardPage (Partial)



## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [ ] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [ ] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [ ] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof

and remove all the sections below.

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Make-a-pull-request).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia's-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-CI-checks-fail-on-your-PR).

pr_title: Milestone 2.3 and 2.4 (Migrate away from protractor): Migrated few test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

Migrated the following test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
**Suites Covered:**
* ExplorationFeedbackTab
* ExplorationHistoryTab
* ExplorationImprovementsTab
* ExplorationStaticticsTab
* ExplorationTranslationTab
* Embedding
* Extensions

**Utils Covered:**
* ExplorationEditorPage (Partial)
* ExplorationPlayerPage (Partial)
* LibraryPage (Partial)
* AdminPage (Partial)
* CreatorDashboardPage (Partial)

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [ ] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [ ] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [ ] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Make-a-pull-request).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia's-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-CI-checks-fail-on-your-PR).

pr_title: Milestone 2.5, 2.6, 2.7 (Migrate away from protractor): Migrated few test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

Migrated the following test suite from protractor to webdriverIO.
**Suites Covered:**
* FeatureGating
* FileUploadFeatures
* FileUploadExtensions
* Library
* PlayVoiceover
* Publication

**Utils Covered:**
* AdminPage (Complete)
* ExplorationEditorPage (Complete)
* LibraryPage (Complete)
* ExplorationPlayerPage (Complete)

## Essential Checklist

- [ ] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Make-a-pull-request).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia's-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-CI-checks-fail-on-your-PR).

#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

<!--

no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,

[{'comment_id': 1006957542, 'comment_body': '`waitFor.pageToFullyLoad` only works when we navigate to preview tab for the first time, on the next time we need to explicitly wait using browser.pause because even adding `visibilityOf` is not working and causing this flake https://github.com/oppia/oppia/actions/runs/3312048155/jobs/5468246555

The screenshot shows that the click happens on the main tab icon but the navigation does not happens because preview tab takes some time to load.
![Full-exploration-editor-should-delete-interactions-cleanly](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/86483059/198314456-7a35f2f1-7505-45cc-b921-432da11c38fe.png)

I was even able to reproduce this on server, the first time we are getting a loading screen but second time no loading screen but click does not work if we click on main tab real quick (webdriverio is too fast)

pr_title: E2E Flake: Fixes Conversation not visible and English in exploration language is not visible
pr_body:
## Overview
<!--
READ ME FIRST:
Please answer *both* questions below and check off every point from the Essential Checklist!
If there is no corresponding issue number, fill in N/A where it says [fill_in_number_here] below in 1.
-->

1. This PR fixes or fixes part of #16444, #16460   and #16098.
2. This PR does the following: Fixes Conversation not visible, Cannot read properties of undefined (reading '$$') and English in exploration language is not visible

## Essential Checklist

- [x] The PR title starts with "Fix #bugnum: ", followed by a short, clear summary of the changes. (If this PR fixes part of an issue, prefix the title with "Fix part of #bugnum: ...".)
- [x] The linter/Karma presubmit checks have passed locally on your machine.
- [x] "Allow edits from maintainers" is checked. (See [here](https://help.github.com/en/github/collaborating-with-issues-and-pull-requests/allowing-changes-to-a-pull-request-branch-created-from-a-fork) for instructions on how to enable it.)
  - This lets reviewers restart your CircleCI tests for you.
- [x] The PR is made from a branch that's **not** called "develop".

## Proof that changes are correct
50 Successful run of History Tab(conversation not visible): https://github.com/ShivamJhaa/oppia/actions/runs/3356586280/jobs/5563898790
50 Successful runs of ContributorDashboard (English not visible): https://github.com/ShivamJhaa/oppia/actions/runs/3356586279/jobs/5563891089
50 successful runs of LearnerDashboard (Cannot read properties of undefine reading $$): https://github.com/ShivamJhaa/oppia/actions/runs/3329605971/jobs/5507035782 

<!--
Add videos/screenshots of the user-facing interface to demonstrate that the changes
made in this PR work correctly. If this PR is for a developer-facing feature,
provide the videos/screenshots of developer-facing interface.

Please also include videos/screenshots of the developer tools
browser console, so that we can be sure that there are no console errors.

If the changes in your PRs are autogenerated via a script and you cannot provide proof
for the changes then please leave a comment "No proof of changes needed because {{Reason}}"
and remove all the sections below.
-->

#### Proof of changes on desktop with slow/throttled network

<!--
Make sure to properly verify that everything works correctly, and that there are
no weird UI mistakes or other problems. Also, if there are any newly added fields,
try to fill them out and test that different inputs are correctly accepted/rejected.

Throttle the network (to 3G) using the browser Developer Tools (see references below).
There should be no performance or UI issues while the network is slow.

References:
 - Chrome: https://css-tricks.com/throttling-the-network/
 - Firefox: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Tools/Network_Monitor/Throttling
-->

#### Proof of changes on mobile phone

<!--
In some cases this is not needed (e.g. for pages that we do not expect to
support mobile phones, or for backend-only features).

Feel free to use the Developer Tools emulator for this.

References:
 - Chrome: https://developer.chrome.com/docs/devtools/device-mode/
 - Firefox: https://firefox-source-docs.mozilla.org/devtools-user/index.html#responsive-design-mode
-->

#### Proof of changes in Arabic language

<!--
If the PR changes the UI, make sure to add screenshots with the site
language set to Arabic as well (we use Arabic as it is a language written from right to left).
-->

## PR Pointers

- Make sure to follow the [instructions for making a code change](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Make-a-pull-request).
- If you need a review or an answer to a question, and don't have permissions to assign people, **leave a comment** like the following: "{{Question/comment}} @{{reviewer_username}} PTAL". Oppiabot will help assign that person for you.
- For what code owners will expect, see the [Code Owner's wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Oppia's-code-owners-and-checks-to-be-carried-out-by-developers).
- Make sure your PR follows conventions in the [style guide](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/Coding-style-guide), otherwise this will lead to review delays.
- Never force push. If you do, your PR will be closed.
- Some of the e2e tests are flaky, and can fail for reasons unrelated to your PR. We are working on fixing this, but in the meantime, if you need to restart the tests, please check the ["If your build fails" wiki page](https://github.com/oppia/oppia/wiki/If-CI-checks-fail-on-your-PR).
pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 1009099372, 'comment_body': 'We need to wait till the exploration is reverted else we are not able to move to player because revert is in process. If we will look at the screenshot then we are still at history tab but we should be present on player in order to get the conversation.
![Screenshot from 2022-10-31 12-55-12](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/86483059/198953897-6c12841b-465d-478e-b65b-357c5d3d6f62.png)

Now we are moving to player tab only after revert is done. This was able to resolve the flake.
', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 10, 31, 7, 26, 18, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ShivamJhaa', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1009099786, 'comment_body': 'They are not needed because we are using `action.click` which by defaults wait for the button to be clickable before clicking on it.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 10, 31, 7, 27, 1, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ShivamJhaa', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1009101529, 'comment_body': 'Debugging doc: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1TMZkHzNFb-Ua_9Y4CQrm630VqhPawtMYDzOZjZW80e4/edit?usp=sharing', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 10, 31, 7, 29, 54, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ShivamJhaa', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1009558567, 'comment_body': "This also seems like a FE bug in that the editor shouldn't be loading until the language list is available. Do you agree? If so, could you file a bug with LaCE quality?", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 10, 31, 15, 31, 8, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'U8NWXD', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1010225216, 'comment_body': '`$$` selector returns undefined when the element is not visible causing this error https://github.com/oppia/oppia/issues/16460, waiting for its visibility before accessing the element through `$$` resolves this flake (as this makes sure the element is visbile before we select it).', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 11, 1, 9, 2, 15, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ShivamJhaa', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1010295724, 'comment_body': 'Sure, thanks', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2022, 11, 1, 10, 35, 28, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'ShivamJhaa', 'type': 'User'}]
